WEBVTT

00:08.167 --> 00:10.042
BENNY:
Previously on Black Cake...

00:10.708 --> 00:15.292
MR. MITCH:
Your mother wanted you to listen
to all seven recordings together.

00:16.207 --> 00:20.792
ELEANOR [on recording]: I must confess
that Eleanor is not my real name.

00:20.792 --> 00:24.125
Forgive me for keeping so many secrets.

00:24.125 --> 00:27.083
- The only way I can get us out of debt
is through this marriage.

00:27.083 --> 00:28.125
- Marriage?

00:28.125 --> 00:29.417
I know my pa.

00:29.417 --> 00:32.333
He'll get his finances in order,
and there won't be a wedding.

00:32.333 --> 00:33.500
- I hope that you're right.

00:33.500 --> 00:35.917
If you change your mind,
come to London and find me.

00:35.917 --> 00:38.833
ELEANOR:
But my father sold his little girl.

00:39.708 --> 00:41.958
[people gasping]

00:41.958 --> 00:44.833
- Your daughter is not only missing,
she's a murder suspect.

00:44.833 --> 00:47.333
- But if we do find her, God help her.

00:47.917 --> 00:50.167
ELEANOR:
In London, my roommate Elly

00:50.167 --> 00:52.917
was the most cheerful person
I had ever met.

00:53.417 --> 00:56.542
COVEY: What if you study geology
at the university in Edinburgh?

00:56.542 --> 00:58.125
- You can't be serious.

00:58.125 --> 00:59.583
- You need to follow your passion.

01:00.167 --> 01:01.333
ELLY:
To Scotland!

01:01.875 --> 01:02.708
[cups clink]

01:03.000 --> 01:05.000
[thudding]

01:05.000 --> 01:06.375
[people screaming]

01:07.125 --> 01:10.375
- But at least we know where Covey is now.

01:10.375 --> 01:12.875
LEONARD: People have been saying
Bunny was too close to Covey.

01:12.875 --> 01:15.042
I don't need to tell you
how dangerous that is.

01:15.583 --> 01:16.917
- This is my family's shop.

01:16.917 --> 01:18.250
- Not anymore.

01:18.250 --> 01:19.542
[Lin grunting]

01:19.542 --> 01:22.208
♪ tense music playing ♪

01:25.542 --> 01:26.542
- Elly.

01:27.125 --> 01:28.250
Elly!

01:29.667 --> 01:31.125
- Happy New Year, Eleanor.

01:31.125 --> 01:33.375
♪

01:35.000 --> 01:38.917
[people screaming]

01:41.708 --> 01:44.042
[metal grinding, thudding]

01:44.917 --> 01:46.250
COVEY:
Elly!

01:46.833 --> 01:47.750
Elly!

01:47.750 --> 01:48.583
[gasps]

01:51.292 --> 01:54.292
♪ solemn music playing ♪

01:56.042 --> 01:58.333
[heavy breaths]

02:04.167 --> 02:05.917
♪

02:14.875 --> 02:17.042
♪

02:18.333 --> 02:20.583
NURSE ETHEL:
Not so fast now, Eleanor.

02:22.083 --> 02:23.333
- How long have I been here?

02:23.958 --> 02:24.958
- One week.

02:26.458 --> 02:27.458
How's your head?

02:28.292 --> 02:31.125
- Throbbing,
but I suppose I shouldn't complain.

02:32.000 --> 02:33.958
I'm here. I'm alive.

02:34.792 --> 02:36.083
- For your headache.

02:36.083 --> 02:37.083
Here, go on.

02:38.333 --> 02:41.125
And yes, you are lucky to have made it.

02:42.167 --> 02:44.292
Three passengers weren't as fortunate.

02:44.958 --> 02:48.250
Two Scottish men were laid to rest
by their families a few days ago.

02:49.000 --> 02:50.917
- And Coventina?

02:53.833 --> 02:56.250
Where is she? I'd like to visit her grave.

02:56.250 --> 02:58.417
- Greyfriars Kirkyard Cemetery.

02:59.792 --> 03:01.625
I'm afraid there's no headstone, dear.

03:02.458 --> 03:04.458
She had no family to claim her remains.

03:04.458 --> 03:06.667
It's a matter of cost, you see?

03:07.458 --> 03:08.458
But don't you worry.

03:09.208 --> 03:11.958
The city put down a wreath in her honor.

03:11.958 --> 03:14.417
I've saved
the newspaper clippings for you.

03:16.375 --> 03:18.000
- Scotland was her dream.

03:19.583 --> 03:22.500
And now here I am,
left to live it without her.

03:25.917 --> 03:27.708
[distant siren wailing]

03:28.292 --> 03:29.500
- I have no job.

03:30.500 --> 03:31.750
No place to stay.

03:31.750 --> 03:34.208
- I've arranged short-term lodging.

03:34.208 --> 03:36.667
There's a room waiting for you
when you're discharged.

03:37.208 --> 03:40.000
If you like it, you can extend your stay.

03:42.458 --> 03:45.000
I found your nursing certificate
in your handbag.

03:46.500 --> 03:48.042
We take care of our own.

03:49.792 --> 03:51.792
♪ light music playing ♪

03:54.792 --> 03:58.917
You'll be discharged when you can walk
to that mirror down there on your own.

04:00.917 --> 04:01.917
- All right.

04:01.917 --> 04:04.000
- Slow down, dear.

04:04.708 --> 04:08.417
You've suffered a severe laceration
on your right leg.

04:08.417 --> 04:11.000
It won't work like it used to,
not for weeks.

04:11.000 --> 04:12.417
- I have to try.

04:13.833 --> 04:15.375
[Covey grunts]
- Eleanor.

04:17.583 --> 04:19.625
Don't overdo it.

04:21.667 --> 04:23.125
Watch that leg.

04:25.750 --> 04:27.417
We'll try again in the morning.

04:30.083 --> 04:34.167
♪

04:40.625 --> 04:43.625
♪

04:51.333 --> 04:52.958
[contents rattling]

04:56.125 --> 05:00.042
ELEANOR: Eleanor Douglas was an orphan
from a remote part of the island.

05:01.500 --> 05:05.833
And whether you knew me
as Covey Lyncook or Coventina Brown,

05:05.833 --> 05:09.000
I was now... officially dead.

05:09.000 --> 05:12.000
♪ solemn music playing ♪

05:18.958 --> 05:21.083
[wincing]

05:26.833 --> 05:27.833
[grunting]

05:29.375 --> 05:31.375
[heavy breaths]

05:32.917 --> 05:34.917
[Covey grunting]

05:39.458 --> 05:41.458
♪

05:42.917 --> 05:45.542
[heavy breaths and grunts]

05:47.542 --> 05:49.542
[straining, grunting]

05:50.625 --> 05:52.625
[heavy breaths]

05:54.250 --> 05:56.333
A door had been opened for me.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.542
And now, it was up to me

06:01.500 --> 06:02.667
to walk through it.

06:03.125 --> 06:05.958
♪

06:09.458 --> 06:13.667
But if I had known
what lay ahead for me as Eleanor Douglas,

06:14.458 --> 06:17.792
I don't know if I ever
would've walked through that door.

06:17.792 --> 06:18.792
Eleanor.

06:19.875 --> 06:20.917
Eleanor.

06:22.417 --> 06:23.417
Eleanor.

06:31.958 --> 06:32.917
[heavy footsteps]
[keys jingling]

06:33.417 --> 06:36.125
- Rent's paid weekly in cash.

06:36.958 --> 06:38.542
No guests.

06:38.542 --> 06:41.292
And no loud island music.

06:41.292 --> 06:45.875
If I hear any complaints,
you'll have to make other arrangements.

06:46.542 --> 06:47.542
- Yes, ma'am.

06:47.542 --> 06:49.583
[straining, panting]

06:51.583 --> 06:52.958
- Do you need help, girl?

06:53.875 --> 06:55.542
- No. I'm fine.

06:55.542 --> 06:59.167
If I don't push through the pain,
I'll never recover.

07:00.250 --> 07:02.583
- The shared facilities are down the hall.

07:05.875 --> 07:10.083
There aren't many islanders in Edinburgh,
let alone in this building,

07:10.083 --> 07:12.250
so you can expect some looks.

07:12.875 --> 07:15.292
Just try and ignore them, would you?

07:17.250 --> 07:18.250
- I understand.

07:21.458 --> 07:23.458
♪ solemn music playing ♪

07:43.458 --> 07:45.417
- You have a job lined up, don't you?

07:46.833 --> 07:49.000
I don't accept late payments.

07:49.000 --> 07:50.667
- I have savings.

07:52.625 --> 07:53.625
- Good.

07:55.458 --> 07:57.458
I'll be back next week to collect.

08:01.250 --> 08:04.292
[birds chirping]
[distant waves crashing]

08:06.042 --> 08:09.042
♪ somber music playing ♪

08:25.375 --> 08:27.375
♪

08:32.250 --> 08:33.458
LITTLE MAN:
Forget that boy.

08:42.875 --> 08:45.167
ELEANOR:
I told myself that the only way to survive

08:45.167 --> 08:49.000
was to keep putting distance
between me and my life before.

08:49.583 --> 08:51.000
To stop looking back,

08:52.542 --> 08:55.542
and to focus on making a life in Scotland.

08:59.792 --> 09:03.000
COVEY: I'm sorry,
could you please repeat the question?

09:03.000 --> 09:04.000
OFFICE MANAGER:
Pardon?

09:04.750 --> 09:07.625
- It's just that I'm still getting used
to the Scottish tongue.

09:08.958 --> 09:10.667
And what a beautiful tongue it is.

09:11.583 --> 09:15.333
- How on earth do you think
you can be a receptionist in my country

09:15.333 --> 09:17.500
if you can't even understand me?

09:18.500 --> 09:21.125
- I'm a fast learner.
I was top of my class.

09:22.083 --> 09:23.458
- In your nursing program?

09:24.208 --> 09:25.292
COVEY:
Yes.

09:25.292 --> 09:28.250
And I'm certain that I'll have
no trouble understanding your clients.

09:29.250 --> 09:32.583
I just-- I need to spend more time
with the Scottish people,

09:32.583 --> 09:34.833
something I very much
look forward to doing.

09:36.750 --> 09:41.708
- Tell me, why do you want
to be a receptionist

09:41.708 --> 09:44.333
when you're trained as a nurse?

09:46.417 --> 09:49.792
- Well, I'm not in
proper physical condition

09:49.792 --> 09:51.458
to work in a hospital,

09:51.458 --> 09:53.250
having just recovered
from the train accident.

09:54.208 --> 09:56.833
- Yes, I've read all about it.

09:57.500 --> 10:00.292
And I'm sorry,
but this is a place of business,

10:00.292 --> 10:02.083
not a charity.

10:03.625 --> 10:06.625
♪ I Need Your Love by
Toots and the Maytals playing ♪

10:07.708 --> 10:08.958
MAN:
Position's been filled.

10:11.125 --> 10:13.625
- But I saw the advertisement
in today's paper.

10:13.625 --> 10:14.625
- It's been filled.

10:15.667 --> 10:17.667
- ♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

10:19.667 --> 10:23.333
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

10:25.958 --> 10:27.042
♪ Ooh-ooh... ♪

10:27.042 --> 10:30.000
WOMAN: Thank you, cheers.
MAN: Nice one, cheers.

10:30.000 --> 10:35.625
- ♪ I heard them say
you're going to leave ♪

10:37.083 --> 10:40.958
♪ But I just don't know why ♪

10:42.417 --> 10:44.958
♪ Somebody say you're gonna deceive... ♪

10:44.958 --> 10:46.708
ELEANOR:
Things were bleak.

10:46.708 --> 10:49.083
I was running out of time and money.

10:50.250 --> 10:53.833
Every rejection
made me feel smaller and smaller.

10:54.542 --> 10:56.042
And I felt myself

10:57.792 --> 10:59.042
disappearing.

10:59.042 --> 11:01.750
- ♪ Know why ♪

11:02.667 --> 11:05.708
♪ You told me there will
never be no other one ♪

11:05.708 --> 11:08.042
♪ To hold me in your arms but you ♪

11:09.250 --> 11:10.917
♪ You should know ♪

11:10.917 --> 11:14.000
♪ Say that you love me ♪

11:14.917 --> 11:17.625
♪ You love me, love me, love me, baby ♪

11:17.625 --> 11:18.708
[Covey wincing]

11:18.708 --> 11:23.917
- ♪ 'Cause I, I need your love with me ♪

11:24.583 --> 11:26.500
[wincing]

11:28.250 --> 11:32.125
♪ light music playing ♪

11:40.750 --> 11:42.750
[indistinct chatter]

11:49.167 --> 11:50.625
PERSON: Alright?
PERSON 2: Alright.

11:52.625 --> 11:54.667
- Oh, Lord!

11:55.167 --> 11:57.083
Not him again.

11:57.083 --> 11:59.167
- Who?
- Who? [chuckles]

11:59.167 --> 12:01.625
You've been watching
that new boy all week.

12:01.625 --> 12:03.292
- Have you seen his backstroke?

12:03.292 --> 12:05.000
- [scoffs] Average at best.

12:05.000 --> 12:07.750
- [laughs] What? Is that jealousy I hear?

12:09.167 --> 12:10.167
Besides,

12:10.917 --> 12:13.000
he's the one
who's been staring at me all week.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.292
- [chuckles] He's a boy.

12:15.292 --> 12:17.375
And just like every other boy we know,

12:17.375 --> 12:18.708
he only wants one thing.

12:19.375 --> 12:20.375
- What?

12:20.375 --> 12:22.375
He can't possibly like me for my mind?

12:22.375 --> 12:23.750
- [scoffs] I'm just saying,

12:23.750 --> 12:26.208
don't be surprised when he gets handsy.

12:26.208 --> 12:27.500
[both laugh]

12:27.500 --> 12:30.042
- Are you worried that's what
Jimmy Patterson would do to you?

12:30.042 --> 12:31.750
Because I think he's sweet.

12:31.750 --> 12:33.458
Hi, Jimmy.
- Stop it!

12:35.000 --> 12:36.167
What are you talking about?

12:36.167 --> 12:37.292
- Oh, come on.

12:37.292 --> 12:40.125
Everyone knows Jimmy's been
in love with you since we were kids.

12:40.125 --> 12:42.750
Why you think he's here every week?

12:43.500 --> 12:45.875
- He wants to be a coach someday.
He's studying.

12:46.458 --> 12:48.208
- Studying what? Your bum?

12:48.208 --> 12:49.375
- Stop it!

12:50.458 --> 12:54.458
- Bunny, he's been
nothing but nice all our lives.

12:54.458 --> 12:55.708
Give him a chance.

12:56.208 --> 12:57.458
- He's not my type.

12:57.458 --> 13:00.542
- [scoffs] You never once had a crush,
let alone a type.

13:00.542 --> 13:02.708
- Because I got
more important things on my mind.

13:03.292 --> 13:04.125
But you?

13:04.667 --> 13:07.917
Go ahead! Fall in love with the new kid.

13:07.917 --> 13:09.417
See how long
it takes for him to get fresh,

13:09.417 --> 13:12.750
and when he does,
[scoffs] don't say I didn't warn you.

13:15.750 --> 13:18.750
♪

13:21.708 --> 13:23.917
[indistinct chatter]

13:26.083 --> 13:27.292
COVEY:
Hey, new kid.

13:27.792 --> 13:29.500
Are you just gonna
keep staring at me forever

13:29.500 --> 13:31.542
or were you planning
to introduce yourself?

13:31.542 --> 13:32.875
- Can't I do both?

13:34.583 --> 13:36.042
I'm Gibbs.

13:36.917 --> 13:37.917
Short for Gilbert.

13:38.958 --> 13:42.542
[chuckles] Guess there's no reason for me
to explain why I shortened it, is there?

13:44.167 --> 13:45.167
- I don't mind it.

13:46.542 --> 13:49.208
- They call you... Dolphin Girl, right?

13:51.583 --> 13:53.167
- I'm the fastest girl on the team.

13:54.500 --> 13:56.000
But you must know that already.

13:56.833 --> 13:58.083
I've seen you watching me.

13:58.083 --> 13:59.208
[Gibbs chuckles]

14:00.250 --> 14:01.667
- Okay. Okay.

14:03.042 --> 14:07.250
So tell me, how do I get to know
the famous Covey Lyncook?

14:07.250 --> 14:08.292
[Covey chuckles]

14:08.917 --> 14:10.542
- Before you can get to know me,

14:10.542 --> 14:12.458
you're gonna have to learn
how to say my name.

14:12.917 --> 14:16.875
♪ Man Smart, Woman Smarter
by The Duke of Iron playing ♪

14:16.875 --> 14:19.333
- ♪ Smarter than man in every way ♪

14:21.292 --> 14:24.083
ELEANOR:
I was no longer Dolphin Girl,

14:24.083 --> 14:26.583
no longer the famous Covey Lyncook.

14:28.292 --> 14:30.958
I had to get
used to my new station in life.

14:34.500 --> 14:37.208
If I had to make myself small to survive,

14:38.333 --> 14:39.333
so be it.

14:40.250 --> 14:41.792
- So you want to be a janitor?

14:43.875 --> 14:44.875
- Yes, sir.

14:55.208 --> 14:56.917
- Have you ever seen a slide rule before?

14:58.250 --> 14:59.500
- I have.

14:59.500 --> 15:00.792
At a shop back home.

15:01.375 --> 15:03.167
A Chinese merchant.

15:03.167 --> 15:04.833
It's easy once you get the hang of it.

15:05.500 --> 15:06.750
- Back home...?

15:07.708 --> 15:08.708
The islands?

15:10.167 --> 15:11.167
- Yes.

15:12.000 --> 15:13.792
I worked part-time.

15:13.792 --> 15:18.583
I ran the register,
took inventory, and-- and I tidied up.

15:20.458 --> 15:23.458
- So, you went from working
at the Chinese merchant to nursing school.

15:26.000 --> 15:27.250
Do you plan to return to nursing

15:27.250 --> 15:29.083
when you've fully recovered
from the accident?

15:30.542 --> 15:31.542
- No.

15:32.250 --> 15:34.208
I never really took to it.

15:34.917 --> 15:38.333
I spent most of my days
cleaning bedpans and commodes,

15:38.333 --> 15:43.000
so... I figured
a janitorial position wasn't too far off.

15:43.000 --> 15:44.000
[grunts in pain]

15:50.417 --> 15:51.542
- You know, I'm having a hard time

15:51.542 --> 15:53.917
imagining someone like you
cleaning our commodes

15:53.917 --> 15:57.292
and... lugging rubbish
up and down three flights of stairs.

16:00.500 --> 16:04.625
- If seeing someone like me
around the office bothers you,

16:05.917 --> 16:07.083
I'll make myself scarce.

16:07.083 --> 16:08.583
You won't even know that I'm here.

16:11.167 --> 16:12.542
- Eleanor, I'm sorry, but, um--

16:16.125 --> 16:17.750
I can't hire you.

16:17.750 --> 16:20.625
- Please, I need this job.
I-I won't make any trouble.

16:20.625 --> 16:23.958
- Not only are you overqualified,
you-- you're clearly in pain, and, um--

16:27.167 --> 16:28.375
it wouldn't sit right with me.

16:31.750 --> 16:34.208
- Understood.
Thank you for your time, sir.

16:34.208 --> 16:35.125
- Wait, I'm not finished.

16:37.417 --> 16:39.417
You are smart, polite,

16:40.208 --> 16:41.208
articulate,

16:42.125 --> 16:43.458
and, well, it's not on your CV,

16:43.458 --> 16:46.083
but you have worked
in a support position back home.

16:46.750 --> 16:49.500
My bookkeepers have gotten behind
on a handful of their accounts.

16:52.042 --> 16:53.375
We could use an assistant.

16:53.875 --> 16:54.875
- Really?

16:54.875 --> 16:56.750
BOSS: You've been through
so much already, Eleanor,

16:56.750 --> 16:58.917
having survived
that horrific train accident.

17:01.458 --> 17:02.792
We'd be lucky to have you.

17:06.792 --> 17:08.583
♪ Du Du Wap by Chuck Josephs playing ♪

17:08.583 --> 17:10.667
- Good morning. Hello.
- Hi.

17:10.667 --> 17:11.667
- Pardon me.

17:14.625 --> 17:19.000
- ♪ Du-du-wap-du, what a magic you do ♪

17:21.625 --> 17:26.250
♪ Du-du-wap-du,
I love no one but you ♪

17:28.917 --> 17:33.542
♪ Please, little girl
Tell me what you're gonna do ♪

17:36.333 --> 17:40.917
♪ Du-du-wap-du, call me Mr. Blue... ♪

17:42.500 --> 17:44.667
ELEANOR:
For the first time in Scotland,

17:46.167 --> 17:47.583
I felt seen.

17:47.583 --> 17:51.000
- ♪ Doo-de-woppa
doo-de-woppa-doo-de-woppa-doo ♪

17:51.000 --> 17:54.542
♪ Doo-de-woppa-doo, doo-de-woppa-doo ♪

17:54.542 --> 17:58.417
♪ Do-doo-de-woppa-doo
Baby, doobie-doobie-doobie ♪

17:58.417 --> 18:02.917
♪ Du-du-wap-du,
You're my heart's desire ♪

18:05.500 --> 18:07.625
♪ One little kiss... ♪

18:07.625 --> 18:10.333
- Good morning.
My name is Eleanor Douglas.

18:10.333 --> 18:12.292
I'm your new assistant bookkeeper.

18:16.167 --> 18:19.583
I'm sorry, were you not notified
that I'd be starting today?

18:21.375 --> 18:23.208
- Until yesterday, we weren't even aware

18:23.208 --> 18:26.000
that there was an open position
in our department.

18:26.000 --> 18:27.750
But our supervisor kindly informed us

18:27.750 --> 18:31.833
that he had hired one
of the janitorial applicants to assist us.

18:32.500 --> 18:33.917
Now I see why.

18:33.917 --> 18:35.583
[bookkeeper chuckles and scoffs]

18:36.625 --> 18:38.250
- I'm grateful for the opportunity.

18:38.250 --> 18:41.250
And I can assure you,
I'm a very hard worker.

18:41.917 --> 18:44.708
I'm eager to help the department
however I can.

18:45.292 --> 18:46.292
- [dryly] How wonderful.

18:47.167 --> 18:48.167
Follow me.

18:49.042 --> 18:51.125
You'll find paper and pencils
at the paper station.

18:51.125 --> 18:53.167
Ink is kept in the supply closet.

18:53.167 --> 18:54.333
And if you're prone to typos,

18:54.333 --> 18:56.375
I suggest you bring
your own correction fluid.

18:57.000 --> 18:58.583
- I understand. Thank you.

18:59.208 --> 19:00.333
- This'll be your desk.

19:03.542 --> 19:06.250
That's an interesting choice
for the office, by the way.

19:06.917 --> 19:09.667
I almost feel like I'm on holiday.
[others snickering]

19:09.667 --> 19:12.333
- Good morning. How are my girls?

19:12.333 --> 19:13.500
BEATRICE:
Very well, thank you.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.458
I was just showing our new hire
around the office.

19:15.458 --> 19:16.750
- Ah, yes, very good.

19:16.750 --> 19:18.708
She'll need some instruction, Beatrice.

19:18.708 --> 19:20.458
I'm sure I can count on you
to get her up to speed

19:20.458 --> 19:21.875
to assist with the backlog.

19:21.875 --> 19:24.208
- Of course. It will be my pleasure.

19:28.125 --> 19:30.208
I'll show you
how to type up invoices later,

19:30.208 --> 19:32.083
but you can start
by organizing these receipts

19:32.083 --> 19:34.625
and logging them
into the corresponding account ledger.

19:35.708 --> 19:37.125
Do you think you can manage that?

19:37.125 --> 19:38.542
- Absolutely.

19:40.292 --> 19:43.583
BEATRICE:
Oh, and since you're so eager to help,

19:43.583 --> 19:46.250
I'm sure the other girls have plenty more
to keep you busy.

19:47.583 --> 19:48.792
[Beatrice chuckles]

19:52.708 --> 19:53.542
[box thuds]

19:55.125 --> 19:57.958
ELEANOR: I should have known
that I was in over my head,

19:58.667 --> 20:00.375
and I should have left.

20:01.708 --> 20:05.750
But I was broke
and alone and... desperate.

20:07.917 --> 20:11.083
And so focused
on just making it through each day,

20:12.708 --> 20:14.792
I couldn't see the danger I was in.

20:21.750 --> 20:24.542
[bookkeepers quietly chattering]

20:32.708 --> 20:35.708
[indistinct chatter]

20:45.125 --> 20:46.125
BEATRICE:
Eleanor?

20:47.542 --> 20:48.542
Eleanor?

20:49.333 --> 20:50.333
Eleanor!

20:51.542 --> 20:52.708
Don't you know your own name?

20:53.708 --> 20:55.000
- Of course, I do.

20:55.625 --> 20:59.833
I-I'm sorry, I, I was just
so focused on these receipts.

20:59.833 --> 21:02.125
- Beatrice, we'll miss the bus.

21:04.083 --> 21:06.208
- If you're going to stay late,
you'll need to lock up.

21:06.208 --> 21:07.750
Turn out the lights before you go.

21:07.750 --> 21:08.750
[keys clinking]

21:11.500 --> 21:12.500
[exhales]

21:14.917 --> 21:15.917
[sighs]

21:15.917 --> 21:16.917
- Eleanor.

21:17.750 --> 21:18.750
Eleanor.

21:19.667 --> 21:20.667
Eleanor.

21:20.667 --> 21:21.958
GIBBS:
Co-vey.

21:22.583 --> 21:23.792
Coh-vey.

21:24.208 --> 21:25.208
Cuh-vey.

21:25.625 --> 21:26.458
- Perfect.

21:26.958 --> 21:28.917
- Covey like lovey.

21:28.917 --> 21:32.667
♪ Perfidia by Phyllis Dillon playing ♪

21:32.667 --> 21:35.750
Here we are. Legends Perch.

21:37.500 --> 21:39.250
Do they have diving cliffs
where you grew up?

21:39.833 --> 21:41.833
- In Galina? Of course.

21:42.458 --> 21:43.917
Some might say the best on the island.

21:45.875 --> 21:49.042
- Well, if you're not too chicken,
maybe you could join me one day.

21:49.042 --> 21:50.417
Show off your skills.

21:51.417 --> 21:53.042
- Well, why wait for one day?

21:53.042 --> 21:56.042
- ♪ Your eyes ♪

21:57.375 --> 22:01.292
♪ Are echoing Perfidia ♪

22:02.292 --> 22:03.625
♪ Forgetful of... ♪

22:03.625 --> 22:04.625
- Ready?

22:04.625 --> 22:06.583
- ♪ ...the promise of love ♪

22:06.583 --> 22:09.250
- Three, two, one.

22:11.125 --> 22:12.833
[Covey and Gibbs yelping]

22:19.375 --> 22:21.917
[both chuckling]

22:31.917 --> 22:33.083
- That was amazing.

22:33.667 --> 22:34.667
Wanna go again?

22:36.583 --> 22:37.750
- Not just yet.

22:38.500 --> 22:39.667
Let me enjoy my tour.

22:41.042 --> 22:43.417
I'm feeling a little less homesick
by the moment.

22:44.917 --> 22:46.458
- Oh, you been homesick?

22:49.083 --> 22:50.583
Why did your family leave Galina?

22:52.208 --> 22:53.292
- We sold our land.

22:54.333 --> 22:56.417
Moving during my final year
of school wasn't easy,

22:56.417 --> 22:58.792
but... now I'm glad we did.

23:00.375 --> 23:01.500
- Oh?

23:02.167 --> 23:03.625
- Otherwise, I never would've met you.

23:06.208 --> 23:07.667
What are your plans after school?

23:08.958 --> 23:11.750
- Ah, I'm going to travel the world,

23:12.375 --> 23:16.458
competing,
swimming in the most exotic countries.

23:17.167 --> 23:18.208
What about you?

23:18.625 --> 23:21.417
- I'm going to university in London
to study law.

23:22.750 --> 23:24.167
- London, huh?

23:24.167 --> 23:25.375
- How's that for exotic?

23:27.000 --> 23:28.208
- So,

23:29.250 --> 23:30.875
I have less than a year with you.

23:31.875 --> 23:34.000
To show you
around Portland Parish, I mean.

23:34.917 --> 23:36.708
- Well, lucky for us, it's a small town.

23:39.750 --> 23:40.750
- Lucky us.

23:43.208 --> 23:45.458
Well, I'm not allowed to date
until I finish school anyway,

23:45.458 --> 23:47.875
so... I guess it's for the best.

23:49.292 --> 23:50.292
- Yeah.

23:51.625 --> 23:53.708
And it's a damn good thing
this isn't a date.

23:56.125 --> 23:57.667
- Stop teasing!

23:58.833 --> 23:59.833
Come back here!

24:03.792 --> 24:05.417
I'm telling you all this because

24:06.833 --> 24:08.792
you'll be in London
by the time I graduate,

24:10.000 --> 24:13.167
and-- and I know we only just met,

24:13.708 --> 24:15.083
but I don't want to wait.

24:16.875 --> 24:18.375
I want to get to know you.

24:20.625 --> 24:21.667
And date you.

24:24.792 --> 24:26.208
And I want you to kiss me.

24:30.792 --> 24:32.417
- You just said
you're not allowed to date.

24:35.583 --> 24:37.792
- Who cares what I said? What do you want?

24:40.083 --> 24:41.083
- To get to know you.

24:42.667 --> 24:44.500
To learn everything there is
to know about you.

24:46.458 --> 24:47.458
Will you let me?

24:50.500 --> 24:52.500
♪

25:00.208 --> 25:01.458
- This is far enough.

25:02.083 --> 25:04.000
Pa will lose it
if he sees me walking with a boy.

25:04.667 --> 25:05.667
- Right.

25:06.292 --> 25:07.292
See you around.

25:08.000 --> 25:08.833
Friend.

25:23.833 --> 25:25.333
- Rah!
[Covey gasps]

25:26.125 --> 25:28.125
- [laughs] Where have you been?

25:28.125 --> 25:30.125
- Jeez! Are you following me?

25:30.125 --> 25:31.542
- No, you idiot!

25:31.542 --> 25:33.000
I just went to the market.

25:33.000 --> 25:34.708
Your father's looking for you, by the way.

25:34.708 --> 25:35.542
- Hmm.

25:35.542 --> 25:36.875
- Where have you been?

25:39.583 --> 25:42.000
Swimming... without me?

25:42.583 --> 25:44.500
- I was showing Gibbs Grant around.

25:44.500 --> 25:45.708
- The new kid?

25:45.708 --> 25:47.917
[scoffs] Are you crazy?

25:47.917 --> 25:49.042
What about your dad?

25:49.042 --> 25:50.208
- What about him?

25:51.292 --> 25:53.083
Gibbs was a perfect gentleman,

25:53.083 --> 25:54.292
and he didn't have to be.

25:54.292 --> 25:57.292
I gave him every opportunity
to prove that he only wanted one thing.

25:57.292 --> 25:59.583
- Hmm.
- All he wants is to get to know me.

25:59.583 --> 26:01.042
- So he says.

26:01.042 --> 26:02.125
- Don't be sore.

26:02.750 --> 26:05.500
We'll do a double non-date sometime,
and you can see for yourself.

26:05.500 --> 26:08.000
Me and Gibbs and you and Jimmy.

26:08.000 --> 26:09.000
- Will you stop with that?

26:09.750 --> 26:11.375
I'm not interested in Jimmy, okay?

26:11.375 --> 26:13.625
- Then we'll find you someone else,
someone you do like.

26:13.625 --> 26:15.125
Someone like Gibbs.

26:15.125 --> 26:16.792
- He's not my type either.

26:16.792 --> 26:18.083
- Then who is?

26:18.083 --> 26:19.458
- I don't know.

26:19.458 --> 26:22.042
- Yes, you do. Come on. Tell me.

26:23.208 --> 26:24.208
Tell me.

26:25.333 --> 26:26.958
- You, okay?

26:28.042 --> 26:29.042
I like you.

26:29.042 --> 26:30.792
- Yeah, well, I know that.
[chuckles]

26:33.458 --> 26:34.458
- Do you?

26:38.292 --> 26:39.792
- You can't say that.

26:40.500 --> 26:42.208
Bunny, you know
rumors can get people killed.

26:43.000 --> 26:44.000
It's dangerous.

26:45.458 --> 26:47.875
- But it doesn't change--
That is who I am.

26:48.958 --> 26:50.708
- I'm not asking you to change.

26:51.250 --> 26:53.458
- No, you're asking me to hide.

26:54.208 --> 26:55.500
- For your own safety.

26:57.250 --> 26:58.667
- You're right, forget it.

27:02.750 --> 27:04.500
- Wait. Wait.

27:04.917 --> 27:05.917
Wait, Bunny!

27:07.333 --> 27:08.625
Bunny, you're my best friend,

27:08.625 --> 27:10.542
and that will never change.

27:13.042 --> 27:14.042
Always.

27:15.667 --> 27:16.667
And I love you.

27:17.333 --> 27:18.333
In my own way.

27:20.667 --> 27:22.208
But you can't ever say that again.

27:28.042 --> 27:29.167
ELEANOR:
Back home,

27:29.167 --> 27:32.833
I had advised
my best friend to hide her true self

27:32.833 --> 27:34.250
in order to survive.

27:43.375 --> 27:45.583
Years later, in Scotland,

27:46.375 --> 27:48.458
I had to take my own advice.

27:49.958 --> 27:52.500
♪ solemn music playing ♪

28:00.042 --> 28:01.125
[shaky breaths]

28:01.125 --> 28:02.708
ELEANOR:
I was meant to disappear,

28:06.583 --> 28:10.625
so maybe it was good that the other women
didn't care to know anything about me.

28:13.583 --> 28:15.417
HELEN: Good morning.
- Morning, Helen.

28:15.417 --> 28:17.500
ELEANOR:
If they didn't want to see me,

28:17.500 --> 28:19.958
I would remain unseen.

28:22.625 --> 28:23.458
[thud]

28:23.458 --> 28:25.500
- Ah! Goddammit!

28:25.500 --> 28:27.583
[Boss grunting]

28:27.583 --> 28:30.125
Eleanor, a little help, please?

28:33.583 --> 28:34.833
- Let me.

28:36.708 --> 28:39.125
- Helen, go find
the first aid kit in the kitchen.

28:39.708 --> 28:40.708
BOSS:
[groans] Easy.

28:41.667 --> 28:43.375
- Let's get you cleaned up.

28:47.333 --> 28:48.333
- You know what's funny?

28:49.167 --> 28:51.583
Never known a nurse
to get faint at the sight of blood.

28:52.958 --> 28:55.958
♪ tense music playing ♪

29:07.000 --> 29:08.667
- Do you want
to go out for a drink tonight?

29:08.667 --> 29:10.750
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah? Me too, yeah!

29:10.750 --> 29:12.542
[both chuckling]

29:12.542 --> 29:14.208
BEATRICE:
Right, back to work.

29:18.375 --> 29:20.708
[bookkeepers chatter indistinctly]

29:33.333 --> 29:35.583
- [softly] Beatrice? Hello.

29:36.708 --> 29:39.250
I hope your lunch was swell.

29:39.750 --> 29:40.958
- [dryly] What is it?

29:44.042 --> 29:46.125
- I've been
poring over these files all morning

29:46.125 --> 29:50.750
and... there appears to be an issue
with the Zunwell account.

29:52.000 --> 29:54.708
- Zunwell? That's my account.

29:54.708 --> 29:55.542
COVEY:
Yes.

29:56.542 --> 29:59.000
Yes, that's why I'm speaking with you now.

30:00.875 --> 30:05.958
I've discovered that some of the invoices
just aren't adding up to our ledgers.

30:05.958 --> 30:06.958
- Not possible.

30:08.625 --> 30:10.333
COVEY:
I've checked three times.

30:11.042 --> 30:12.625
There's an issue, no question.

30:13.542 --> 30:15.250
I only wanted
to bring it to your attention

30:15.250 --> 30:16.792
so that you could fix it.

30:16.792 --> 30:18.458
- There's nothing to fix.

30:18.458 --> 30:21.500
Just how hard
did you hit your head in that accident?

30:21.500 --> 30:23.125
[group snickering]

30:24.375 --> 30:27.417
- Your job is to
file receipts and ledgers,

30:28.125 --> 30:29.125
nothing more.

30:30.958 --> 30:33.458
- But I can't just ignore this.

30:33.458 --> 30:35.917
It could come back on me or you.

30:36.417 --> 30:37.917
- Nothing's going to come back on you

30:37.917 --> 30:40.000
because no one's
paying any attention to you.

30:40.000 --> 30:43.792
Before you hobbled in here
with that sad face and pathetic story,

30:43.792 --> 30:46.000
this job didn't even exist.

30:46.000 --> 30:49.750
It doesn't matter how late you stay
or how much extra work you do,

30:50.542 --> 30:54.250
you will never be
anything more than a pity hire.

31:12.208 --> 31:13.667
BEATRICE:
You don't want to get too drunk tonight.

31:13.667 --> 31:16.333
[women laughing]
[indistinct chatter]

31:31.000 --> 31:34.000
♪

31:43.375 --> 31:44.750
[knock on door]
BOSS: Yes?

31:47.208 --> 31:48.208
- Excuse me.

31:48.833 --> 31:50.500
I hate to interrupt.

31:51.292 --> 31:53.292
- That's all right.
[sighs] I could use a break.

31:54.292 --> 31:56.458
At this hour,
all the figures are morphing into one.

31:57.333 --> 31:58.708
- You work so hard.

31:59.333 --> 32:00.750
Anyway, sir,

32:02.083 --> 32:05.792
I found something that I thought
I ought to bring to your attention.

32:05.792 --> 32:07.625
Hopefully, it's nothing.

32:08.750 --> 32:09.750
- What did you find?

32:10.333 --> 32:13.083
- Discrepancies. In the Zunwell account.

32:14.875 --> 32:16.542
- I'm sure it's just a misunderstanding.

32:18.000 --> 32:19.125
Have you told Beatrice?

32:20.375 --> 32:21.375
- Yes, but--

32:22.750 --> 32:27.458
I don't think she trusted that
I was capable or qualified to do so,

32:28.542 --> 32:29.833
and I don't want to upset her.

32:31.167 --> 32:32.542
It's hard enough doing my job

32:32.542 --> 32:35.542
when the other women
clearly don't think I deserve to have it.

32:39.792 --> 32:41.417
- Right, I'll look into this
in the morning.

32:42.792 --> 32:45.458
In the meantime,
no matter what the girls say,

32:46.542 --> 32:47.833
you deserve to be here.

32:49.917 --> 32:51.417
[sniffling]

32:52.625 --> 32:54.458
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry, I-I--

32:54.958 --> 32:55.958
- Oh, God, uh...

32:57.958 --> 32:59.083
Would you like a tissue?

32:59.083 --> 33:02.458
- [sniffling] I'm so sorry.
I don't know what's gotten into me.

33:06.458 --> 33:07.458
- I think I do.

33:08.000 --> 33:09.000
- You do?

33:10.583 --> 33:13.125
BOSS: Does it have anything to do
with the fact that you're not a nurse?

33:16.875 --> 33:17.875
- Pardon?

33:17.875 --> 33:19.750
- Well, a trained nurse
would've jumped to action

33:19.750 --> 33:21.000
if someone cut themselves.

33:23.750 --> 33:25.792
- Sir, I mentioned before

33:26.750 --> 33:29.333
that I didn't take to nursing, remember?

33:29.333 --> 33:30.833
- Aye, but you just stood there, frozen,

33:31.875 --> 33:33.292
as if you'd never been trained at all.

33:36.000 --> 33:38.000
♪ tense music playing ♪

33:42.750 --> 33:43.750
- You're right.

33:45.000 --> 33:46.375
I'm not a nurse.

33:48.042 --> 33:51.167
I padded my CV
by using a friend's experience.

33:52.000 --> 33:54.500
I was just so desperate for work,

33:54.500 --> 33:56.042
I didn't know what else to do.

33:58.083 --> 34:02.417
But if you give me another chance,
I promise I will work twice as hard.

34:03.000 --> 34:06.917
I will work overtime without pay,
I'll-- I'll do anything.

34:08.250 --> 34:10.875
Please... don't fire me.

34:10.875 --> 34:11.875
- It's okay.

34:13.792 --> 34:15.250
You've suffered enough.

34:16.417 --> 34:19.417
As long as I can trust that you'll be
transparent with me moving forward,

34:19.417 --> 34:20.625
your job is secure.

34:23.708 --> 34:25.167
Can I trust you, Eleanor?

34:26.042 --> 34:27.292
- Yes, sir, absolutely.

34:29.833 --> 34:31.208
- Then we won't speak of this again.

34:36.667 --> 34:37.667
And Eleanor?

34:40.083 --> 34:42.333
I don't want you
getting wrapped up in women's nonsense.

34:43.375 --> 34:44.917
If there's anything you need

34:44.917 --> 34:47.083
and you feel uncomfortable
asking one of them,

34:47.083 --> 34:48.292
you come directly to me.

34:50.208 --> 34:51.375
I'll take care of you.

34:53.208 --> 34:54.208
- [softly] Thank you.

35:00.208 --> 35:03.208
♪ tense music continues ♪

35:05.125 --> 35:06.042
[sharp exhale]

35:16.292 --> 35:17.292
BOSS:
Beatrice!

35:20.542 --> 35:21.542
Beatrice!

35:22.250 --> 35:24.167
- She's in the break room eating lunch.

35:25.167 --> 35:26.583
BOSS: Beatrice!
- I'll get her.

35:27.250 --> 35:28.667
- What's all the yelling about?

35:29.500 --> 35:31.917
- I spent the entire morning
going through the Zunwell files.

35:33.375 --> 35:37.708
And I discovered an error.
Well, a pattern of errors, actually.

35:38.292 --> 35:41.125
A pattern that has likely
cost this company thousands of pounds.

35:42.083 --> 35:43.417
And thanks to Eleanor,

35:43.417 --> 35:46.250
I'll be able to put a stop
to this hemorrhaging of funds immediately.

35:47.750 --> 35:48.917
- Are you sure?

35:48.917 --> 35:52.250
- I spent the entire morning
going over your work.

35:52.250 --> 35:54.875
- I apologize.
I don't know how I missed it.

35:54.875 --> 35:57.417
- I do. You ignored your colleague,

35:57.417 --> 36:00.875
who was only looking out for you
and this company, might I add.

36:00.875 --> 36:03.417
- It won't happen again.
- [scoffs] It sure as hell won't.

36:03.917 --> 36:04.917
From this point on,

36:04.917 --> 36:06.917
Eleanor will crosscheck
all of your accounts

36:06.917 --> 36:09.292
to make sure
there are no further discrepancies.

36:10.042 --> 36:11.042
- Of course.

36:11.875 --> 36:14.833
I'll get right on top of it and deliver
all of the files to Eleanor this evening.

36:15.417 --> 36:16.667
We'll go through them together.

36:17.625 --> 36:18.625
I'll stay late with her.

36:19.125 --> 36:20.417
- Right, well, you get started.

36:21.500 --> 36:24.000
But Eleanor won't be staying late
to clean up your mess tonight.

36:25.875 --> 36:27.333
She's having dinner with me.

36:28.167 --> 36:29.542
See you here at 6:30.

36:32.000 --> 36:35.000
♪ tense music playing ♪

36:39.917 --> 36:40.750
[office door shuts]

36:41.125 --> 36:43.542
ELEANOR:
I didn't know what to expect.

36:46.250 --> 36:48.208
But he knew part of my story,

36:49.208 --> 36:51.083
and if I wanted him to keep it to himself,

36:52.917 --> 36:54.833
I needed to just go to dinner with him...

36:55.542 --> 36:57.333
BUS CONDUCTOR:
Wanstead Road.

36:58.083 --> 36:59.833
ELEANOR:
...and ask questions later.

37:00.875 --> 37:02.375
COVEY:
Where have you taken me?

37:03.833 --> 37:05.000
What is this place?

37:05.750 --> 37:06.750
GIBBS:
My family's land.

37:07.250 --> 37:09.667
I used to come up here
and sit here every day after school.

37:11.708 --> 37:13.750
Back then, I thought
I'd be a farmer like my dad.

37:14.708 --> 37:15.708
We all thought that.

37:16.500 --> 37:18.292
COVEY:
And why did your parents sell it?

37:19.792 --> 37:21.500
- We were forced out by a mining company.

37:22.167 --> 37:23.333
Our whole village was.

37:24.250 --> 37:26.167
And nobody knew
how to stop it from happening.

37:27.625 --> 37:28.750
It was humiliating.

37:29.917 --> 37:31.125
Especially for my dad.

37:35.875 --> 37:36.875
- It's beautiful.

37:38.292 --> 37:39.667
- It's about to be destroyed.

37:41.708 --> 37:43.833
So I wanted
to see it one last time with you.

37:48.208 --> 37:49.667
COVEY:
My pa lost everything too.

37:50.167 --> 37:51.250
First his family,

37:52.125 --> 37:54.667
when he went against their wishes
and chose my mom over them.

37:57.708 --> 37:59.083
And then, he lost her as well.

38:02.708 --> 38:03.708
- Did she pass?

38:06.500 --> 38:08.292
- She left us when I was 11.

38:12.667 --> 38:13.667
- Covey,

38:14.917 --> 38:18.333
losing land is one thing,
but losing your mother...?

38:21.958 --> 38:23.000
I can't imagine.

38:27.458 --> 38:29.958
- Maybe one day,
when Bunny and I become famous swimmers,

38:29.958 --> 38:33.958
she'll show up at one of our competitions
and surprise me.

38:38.750 --> 38:40.292
That's silly, I know.

38:40.292 --> 38:41.458
- No, that's--

38:41.458 --> 38:42.458
That's not silly.

38:44.500 --> 38:45.500
That's love.

38:48.167 --> 38:50.917
And I know I can't go back
and change what happened to my family,

38:52.292 --> 38:53.292
but when I'm a lawyer,

38:54.042 --> 38:57.333
maybe I can stop that kind of thing
from happening to somebody else.

39:01.042 --> 39:02.417
- I believe you will, Gibbs.

39:03.083 --> 39:04.083
I do.

39:04.583 --> 39:05.583
- I know you do.

39:06.875 --> 39:09.167
And you are going to be
an amazing mother someday.

39:11.167 --> 39:12.833
The kind of mother you deserved.

39:14.167 --> 39:15.000
[chuckles]

39:17.250 --> 39:18.667
- You have the biggest heart.

39:19.417 --> 39:21.042
That's what I love most about you.

39:22.917 --> 39:23.750
And,

39:26.167 --> 39:28.958
I've enjoyed getting to know you
these past few months.

39:30.667 --> 39:32.417
But even more than that--

39:35.417 --> 39:36.417
- Covey,

39:39.417 --> 39:40.417
may I kiss you?

39:42.000 --> 39:45.000
♪ light music playing ♪

39:52.500 --> 39:55.667
ELEANOR:
Gibbs saw me for who I really was,

39:55.667 --> 39:58.000
and also for who I wanted to be.

40:00.125 --> 40:01.333
If I had known then

40:01.333 --> 40:04.833
that I'd spend the rest of my life
hiding the girl he loved,

40:05.625 --> 40:08.417
I would've stayed
on that farm with him forever.

40:09.458 --> 40:10.542
[approaching footsteps]

40:17.083 --> 40:18.083
[knock on door]

40:20.375 --> 40:23.667
- Oh! If it isn't the woman of the hour!

40:25.583 --> 40:27.458
Come, please. Come in!

40:30.042 --> 40:30.875
Oh.

40:33.208 --> 40:36.583
I think I've read every article
written about the train accident.

40:37.875 --> 40:40.292
Do you remember it much
or is it all a blur?

40:40.875 --> 40:43.083
- Well, I try
not to think about it too much.

40:43.083 --> 40:44.542
- Oh, of course.

40:44.542 --> 40:46.750
My husband told me about your leg injury.

40:46.750 --> 40:48.167
How are you getting around?

40:49.417 --> 40:52.042
- I'm doing much better,
now that I have a job.

40:52.042 --> 40:54.333
- Oh, well, not to toot my own horn,

40:54.333 --> 40:56.250
but my keen interest in the accident

40:56.250 --> 40:59.292
is probably what inspired him
to hire you in the first place.

40:59.792 --> 41:00.792
- Is that so?

41:01.708 --> 41:03.625
MILDRED: You probably haven't seen
much evidence of it,

41:03.625 --> 41:06.042
but there is
a small Caribbean population here.

41:06.042 --> 41:09.833
We believe it's time our people start
to welcome yours with open arms.

41:10.542 --> 41:12.542
Hiring you is only the beginning.

41:13.500 --> 41:15.042
- We'd like to host an event.

41:16.083 --> 41:17.083
In your honor.

41:18.708 --> 41:19.542
- For me?

41:20.333 --> 41:21.333
Why?

41:21.333 --> 41:23.375
I mean, thank you.

41:23.958 --> 41:24.875
But why?

41:24.875 --> 41:28.875
MILDRED:
To shine a light on your struggles
as a survivor of that tragic accident,

41:28.875 --> 41:31.167
whilst also celebrating your successes,

41:31.167 --> 41:32.917
like working for the trading company.

41:34.750 --> 41:36.417
- What would I have to do?

41:36.417 --> 41:37.917
- Tell your story.

41:37.917 --> 41:39.750
Talk about your island upbringing

41:39.750 --> 41:42.000
and your experience
recovering from the accident

41:42.000 --> 41:44.333
while making your way in a foreign land.

41:44.750 --> 41:46.458
We'll invite the press.

41:46.458 --> 41:49.458
They'll be sure
to put your photo and name in the paper.

41:49.458 --> 41:51.292
It'll be a coming-out, if you will.

41:53.625 --> 41:57.375
- Oh, I'm not too sure I-I-I do well
under the spotlight.

41:57.375 --> 41:58.583
I tend to clam up.

41:58.583 --> 42:00.750
- Nonsense. You're so articulate.

42:00.750 --> 42:02.542
- And the press
would be great for the business.

42:03.083 --> 42:05.500
♪

42:07.333 --> 42:10.875
- Maybe there's another way we can
acknowledge the good the company is doing

42:10.875 --> 42:12.500
by trading with the islands,

42:12.500 --> 42:14.333
rather than make it about me.

42:17.542 --> 42:21.042
- Smart girl.
I think you're onto something.

42:21.042 --> 42:23.125
We'll broaden our focus.

42:23.125 --> 42:25.542
Yes. It doesn't have to be about you.

42:25.542 --> 42:27.167
We'll make it a fundraiser

42:27.167 --> 42:29.792
in honor of your friend who passed,
Coventina Brown.

42:29.792 --> 42:30.792
[Covey coughing]

42:30.792 --> 42:34.583
- Oh, can you imagine
being laid to rest without a headstone?

42:34.583 --> 42:37.792
Nameless!
As if the poor girl didn't exist at all.

42:38.625 --> 42:42.042
It's a travesty our community hasn't yet
raised the funds to purchase one.

42:43.000 --> 42:44.792
You don't have to tell your story,

42:44.792 --> 42:46.917
but you could say a few words
about your friend.

42:48.583 --> 42:49.583
- Well, I love it.

42:49.583 --> 42:50.583
[Mildred laughs]

42:51.250 --> 42:52.583
- What do you say, Eleanor?

42:57.250 --> 42:58.625
- I'll do it.

42:58.625 --> 43:01.083
- Oh, how wonderful!

43:01.625 --> 43:03.083
- It would be an honor.

43:03.083 --> 43:03.917
[glasses clink]

43:11.125 --> 43:12.250
[knock on door]

43:12.250 --> 43:13.250
- Afternoon.

43:13.833 --> 43:16.125
I have a stack of ledgers
I double-checked,

43:16.125 --> 43:17.458
I just need you to sign off.

43:18.292 --> 43:19.292
BOSS:
Come in.

43:19.958 --> 43:22.917
Oh, shut the door behind you. Please.

43:28.708 --> 43:30.083
- Is everything okay?

43:30.542 --> 43:32.625
- I've decided not to hold the fundraiser.

43:34.792 --> 43:36.375
- I'm sorry to hear that.

43:37.083 --> 43:37.917
- Are you?

43:39.833 --> 43:40.833
- Pardon?

43:43.250 --> 43:45.583
- You know, I've been thinking a lot
about your story.

43:47.083 --> 43:48.708
How you moved up here to Scotland,

43:49.417 --> 43:51.208
a place where you knew no one,

43:51.958 --> 43:54.292
and how you could've
just returned to England

43:54.292 --> 43:56.000
or the islands after the accident.

43:57.542 --> 43:59.625
To your family, your friends.

44:01.083 --> 44:02.958
Then last night,
it all started to come together.

44:04.250 --> 44:05.833
You lied about your training,

44:06.375 --> 44:09.167
and you're afraid to tell your story
because you're still lying.

44:10.958 --> 44:12.750
You're running from something, aren't you?

44:16.292 --> 44:17.292
What are you running from?

44:24.000 --> 44:25.000
- [voice breaking] I'm sorry.

44:25.542 --> 44:27.458
I'm so sorry,
I never meant to cause any trouble.

44:27.458 --> 44:29.292
I'll see myself out.
- It's gonna be okay.

44:30.375 --> 44:32.292
[Covey breathing shakily]

44:32.292 --> 44:33.292
- Trust me.

44:34.042 --> 44:35.083
- I don't see how.

44:35.083 --> 44:37.083
[shushing]

44:48.292 --> 44:50.583
- No, I'm-- I'm sorry. No.

44:50.583 --> 44:52.083
No. Please stop.

44:53.458 --> 44:55.458
[grunts, shaky breaths]

44:57.125 --> 44:58.500
[zipper unzipping]

45:01.875 --> 45:05.125
ELEANOR: It was as if
everything had been frozen inside.

45:08.250 --> 45:11.375
The only thing I could control
in that moment was my mind.

45:13.750 --> 45:15.000
So I escaped

45:16.750 --> 45:17.958
as best I could.

45:21.333 --> 45:23.333
[both laughing]

45:25.625 --> 45:28.000
♪ sinister music playing ♪

45:31.125 --> 45:34.917
ELEANOR:
You grow up thinking that when someone
does something terrible to you,

45:35.583 --> 45:37.000
you will react,

45:37.000 --> 45:38.333
you will fight back,

45:39.542 --> 45:41.083
you will run away.

45:47.750 --> 45:50.875
I had already proven myself
capable of doing this.

45:52.500 --> 45:53.333
[sharp inhale]

45:58.708 --> 46:00.333
But this time was different.

46:00.333 --> 46:01.542
LITTLE MAN:
Ladies and gentlemen,

46:02.333 --> 46:04.375
raise your glasses, please, for a toast.

46:05.833 --> 46:07.083
To my wife!

46:07.083 --> 46:08.875
[all cheering]

46:11.667 --> 46:12.500
[camera shutter clicks]

46:12.833 --> 46:14.417
[guests cheer and applaud]

46:14.417 --> 46:16.542
♪ band plays upbeat calypso music ♪

46:16.958 --> 46:18.917
[guests chattering indistinctly]

46:20.375 --> 46:23.667
- I bought us the best suite here
for our first night as man and wife.

46:25.792 --> 46:26.875
I'm looking forward to it.

46:29.042 --> 46:30.042
Aren't you?

46:31.167 --> 46:33.125
I got my eyes and ears
all over this island.

46:35.000 --> 46:37.792
You think I don't know that you've been
sneaking round with Gibbs Grant?

46:41.583 --> 46:42.958
You belong to me now.

46:44.833 --> 46:45.833
Understand?

46:46.708 --> 46:48.708
[chuckles] Forget that boy.

46:50.917 --> 46:51.917
Or he's dead.

46:52.833 --> 46:53.833
PHOTOGRAPHER:
Big smile.

46:53.833 --> 46:54.750
[shutter clicks]

46:55.708 --> 46:58.417
- All right. That's enough.

47:01.583 --> 47:04.583
[indistinct chatter]

47:11.792 --> 47:13.375
♪ song ends ♪
[guests applaud]

47:16.250 --> 47:17.958
♪ band plays new upbeat song ♪

47:29.250 --> 47:31.083
[plates crashing]
[people gasping]

47:33.750 --> 47:35.750
[footsteps echoing]

47:35.750 --> 47:38.750
♪ solemn music playing ♪

48:01.000 --> 48:04.000
[breathing shakily]

48:12.750 --> 48:14.500
[panting sharply]

48:19.583 --> 48:20.625
[door opens]

48:25.042 --> 48:26.292
- I tried to warn you.

48:34.708 --> 48:37.042
He started paying extra attention to me

48:39.125 --> 48:42.333
right after my husband
left me and my little boy destitute.

48:45.292 --> 48:46.583
He knew that I needed him.

48:48.167 --> 48:49.792
And when he cornered me,

48:51.708 --> 48:54.250
he knew that
no one would believe me if I told.

48:57.375 --> 48:58.875
That's why he chose you.

49:03.250 --> 49:04.500
- Why don't you leave?

49:06.167 --> 49:07.167
- [voice breaking] My son.

49:09.417 --> 49:11.750
I'm not going to dwell on it
for the rest of my life.

49:13.500 --> 49:14.667
I do what I can.

49:15.708 --> 49:16.708
I show up.

49:17.875 --> 49:19.750
I act as if it never happened.

49:26.000 --> 49:27.333
That's what you'll do, Eleanor.

49:28.833 --> 49:29.833
Every day.

49:30.875 --> 49:32.375
Until you really do forget.

49:36.250 --> 49:37.542
- But you haven't forgotten.

49:39.208 --> 49:40.208
Have you?

49:45.583 --> 49:46.667
- Clean yourself up.

49:48.333 --> 49:50.500
You'll be okay. [sniffs]

49:54.792 --> 49:59.250
ELEANOR: Bunny had warned me
that boys only wanted one thing.

50:02.625 --> 50:04.167
Was Gibbs an anomaly?

50:05.167 --> 50:07.500
Was he the only one who saw me,

50:08.500 --> 50:11.042
who wanted more than my body?

50:11.042 --> 50:12.000
[sharp exhale]

50:17.875 --> 50:20.875
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

50:45.042 --> 50:47.583
But it wasn't just Bunny who warned me.

50:50.833 --> 50:52.375
My pa did too.

50:59.167 --> 51:02.500
I saw my pa in that frigid water.

51:04.542 --> 51:07.792
And in that moment, all was forgotten.

51:10.500 --> 51:14.333
I wanted to be with him,
wherever that was.

51:16.167 --> 51:19.292
What would he think
if he could see me in the Scottish sea?

51:21.625 --> 51:24.125
Would he apologize for pushing me away?

51:27.125 --> 51:30.583
Or would Pa wrap his arms around me

51:32.167 --> 51:33.417
and say nothing?

51:37.125 --> 51:38.417
Would he pull me under

51:41.792 --> 51:43.333
and take me back home?

51:46.042 --> 51:49.042
[muffled screaming]

51:54.208 --> 51:56.208
[Pearl grunting]

52:07.625 --> 52:10.792
PEARL:
You've always been a cowardly man, Lin.

52:10.792 --> 52:12.458
But this? [scoffs]

52:14.333 --> 52:16.250
- I just want a beer. Will you please--

52:16.250 --> 52:17.750
PEARL:
So you can drink yourself to death?

52:17.750 --> 52:19.708
No. I don't think I will.

52:19.708 --> 52:23.292
I am done helping you destroy your life.

52:24.083 --> 52:25.833
I didn't wind up on the beach by chance.

52:26.333 --> 52:28.208
I've been looking for you all day.

52:28.208 --> 52:32.042
The police, they think they know
who poisoned Little Man.

52:33.583 --> 52:34.792
- Was it that Grant boy?

52:35.708 --> 52:37.333
Did he turn up?
PEARL: No.

52:38.000 --> 52:40.208
The man goes by the name Short Shirt.

52:41.708 --> 52:44.458
They aren't sure
how he got to Little Man that night,

52:45.792 --> 52:47.083
but he's down at the station.

52:47.083 --> 52:49.583
They're questioning him as we speak.
[Lin scoffs]

52:49.583 --> 52:50.958
- What's funny?

52:50.958 --> 52:51.958
- You.

52:52.875 --> 52:53.875
You pretending to believe

52:53.875 --> 52:56.375
that someone who had nothing
to do with our Covey killed him.

52:56.375 --> 52:59.750
- His arrest has cleared your name
for the time being.

52:59.750 --> 53:01.208
If I were you,

53:01.708 --> 53:05.417
I'd do like my wife and daughter,
and disappear.

53:08.458 --> 53:11.292
'Cause I won't be cleaning up
any more of your messes.

53:11.750 --> 53:12.583
No.

53:14.375 --> 53:15.583
You're on your own now.

53:18.542 --> 53:19.458
- What, you're quitting?

53:20.208 --> 53:21.208
How will I eat?

53:21.208 --> 53:22.292
[Pearl scoffs]

53:30.042 --> 53:31.708
- I started working here

53:32.375 --> 53:33.500
for Mathilda.

53:34.917 --> 53:36.625
I stayed for Covey,

53:37.542 --> 53:39.083
so she would have someone.

53:39.667 --> 53:42.375
Someone other than you
to look out for her.

53:43.792 --> 53:44.792
But now,

53:45.417 --> 53:47.792
she's-- she's dead.

53:49.625 --> 53:52.792
And if you hadn't pissed away
your money, your business,

53:54.250 --> 53:55.542
and your dignity,

53:56.500 --> 53:58.042
she'd still be here.

53:58.042 --> 54:01.208
Mathilda... would still be here.

54:03.958 --> 54:06.792
So as much as I pity you, Lin,

54:09.625 --> 54:12.250
I no longer feel obligated
to work for you.

54:14.708 --> 54:17.542
I have to live my own life.

54:19.667 --> 54:21.708
I suggest you do the same.

54:23.208 --> 54:24.208
Now that you,

54:24.792 --> 54:26.125
for some reason,

54:26.708 --> 54:28.542
